The QM/MM interface parameters define the interaction between classical and quantum regions. 

  qmmm
  [ [[qmmm_eref       |eref]] <double precision default 0.0d0>]
  [ [[qmmm_bq_zone    |bqzone]] <double precision default 9.0d0>]
  [ [[qmmm_mm_charges |mm_charges]] [exclude <(none||all||linkbond||linkbond_H) default none>]
           [ expand  <none||all||solute||solvent> default none]
           [ update  <integer default 0>] 
  [ [[qmmm_link_atoms |link_atoms]] <(hydrogen||halogen) default hydrogen>]
  [ [[qmmm_link_ecp   |link_ecp]]  <(auto||user) default auto>]
  [ [[qmmm_region     |region]]   < [region1]  [region2]  [region3] > ]
  [ [[qmmm_method     |method]]   [method1]  [method2]  [method3]  ]
  [ [[qmmm_maxiter    |maxiter]]  [maxiter1] [maxiter2] [maxiter3] ]
  [ [[qmmm_ncycles    |ncycles]]  < [number] default 1 > ]
  [ [[qmmm_density    |density]]  [espfit] [static] [dynamical] ]
  [ [[qmmm_xyz     |xyz]]  ]
  [ [[qmmm_convergence     |convergence]] <double precision default 1.0d-4>] ]
  [ [[qmmm_rename   |rename]] ] <filename>
  [ [[qmmm_nsamples|nsamples]] ]
  end


